00041 /// @name Legacy printers without context parameter
00042 //@{
00043 /// Disassemble the decoded instruction using the ATT SYSV syntax. The
00044 /// output buffer must be at least 16 bytes long. Returns true if
00045 /// disassembly proceeded without errors.
00046 /// @param xedd a #xed_decoded_inst_t for a decoded instruction
00047 /// @param out_buffer a buffer to write the disassembly in to.
00048 /// @param buffer_len maximum length of the disassembly buffer
00049 /// @param runtime_instruction_address the address of the instruction being disassembled. If zero, the offset is printed for relative branches. If nonzero, XED attempts to print the target address for relative branches.
00050 /// @return Returns 0 if the disassembly fails, 1 otherwise.
00051 ///@ingroup PRINT
00052 XED_DLL_EXPORT xed_bool_t
00053 xed_format_att(xed_decoded_inst_t* xedd,
00054                char* out_buffer,
00055                xed_uint32_t buffer_len,
00056                xed_uint64_t runtime_instruction_address);
00057

00073 /// Disassemble the decoded instruction using the XED syntax providing all
00074 /// operand resources (implicit, explicit, suppressed). The output buffer

00076 /// without errors. 
00077 /// @param xedd a #xed_decoded_inst_t for a decoded instruction
00078 /// @param out_buffer a buffer to write the disassembly in to.
00079 /// @param buffer_len maximum length of the disassembly buffer
00080 /// @param runtime_instruction_address the address of the instruction being disassembled. If zero, the offset is printed for relative branches. If nonzero, XED attempts to print the target address for relative branches.
00081 /// @return Returns 0 if the disassembly fails, 1 otherwise.
00082 ///@ingroup PRINT
